Variable By_source_emission_s
Title: By source emission size beyond which aerial always dominates
Units: kgh
Description: The emission size beyond which the cumulative emissions from aerially detected emissions (including a partial detection correction) are consistently higher than for aerially visible emissions simluated from the Rutherford distribution.
Definition: FOR jj := Run DO BEGIN~
	VAR init := Min(Subset(Point_at_which_aeria[Run=jj]));~
	IF init=Null~
		THEN Aerial_min_detected_~
	ELSE init~
END
