Variable Key_results
Title: Key results
Description: The main results to report in Sherwin et al. 2023.~
-Run #: Number identifying the run in question. A run is a full simulation of a selected scenario.~
-Batch counter: Each scenario run often includes multiple batches of Monte Carlo iterations, run in series to circumvent memory and CPU limitations. This tracks each batch through a numerical identifier of 1-10.~
-Scenario: The scenario to run, including the aerial campaign, basin, year, any additional geographic restrictions, etc.~
-Prod simulation (t/h): Estimated scenario-wide production emissions in metric tons per hour from the Rutherford et al. simulation.~
-Prod simulation P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Prod simulation P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Prod aerial (t/h): Estimated scenario-wide production emissions from aerially measured plumes above the transition point, in metric tons per hour.~
-Prod aerial P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Prod aerial P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Prod partial (t/h): Estimated scenario-wide production emissions implied due to partial detection based on aerially measured plumes above the transition point, in metric tons per hour.~
-Prod partial P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Prod partial P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Prod emissions (t/h): Estimated scenario wide emission from production sites (well sites) after combining data from all available sources.~
-Prod emissions P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Prod emissions P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
Aerial midstream emissions (t/h): Estimated scenario-wide midstream emissions from aerially measured plumes, in metric tons per hour.~
-Aerial midstream emissions P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Aerial midstream emissions P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Midstream partial detect (t/h): Estimated scenario-wide midstream emissions implied due to partial detection based on aerially measured plumes, in metric tons per hour.~
-Midstream GHGI below min detect (t/h): Estimated scenario-wide midstream emissions below the aerial detection limit, estimated using EPA Greenhouse Gas Inventory data, presented in metric tons per hour~
-Total emissions (t/h): Total estimated emissions after combining all data sources, including production and midstream, in metric tons per hour.~
-Total emissions P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total emissions P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-N: The total number of Monte Carlo iterations in the selected run, including all batches.~
-% SDev of MC iterations: The standard deviation of total estimated emissions across production and midstream across all Monte Carlo iterations in the selected run. Computed over percent deviations in each iteration from the mean over the full run.~
-Min detected emission: The smallest detected emission in each campaign, computed using initial mean quantification estimates provided by each team, without controlled release corrections.~
-Transition point: The emission size beyond which (≥) to use aerially measured emissions instead of simulated emissions for well sites. Averaged over all Monte Carlo iterations in the selected run.~
-Total covered production (t(CH4)/hr): Total methane production from well sites surveyed at least once by the aerial campaign (weighted average over months in which a well site was surveyed).~
-Wells covered: Total count of wells covered in the selected scenario.~
-Well visits: Total well visits in the selected scenario, including each aerial visit to a well as a separate measurement.~
-Wells per site: Average wells per site in the selected basin/region.~
-# production plumes: Total number of aerially detect production plumes from the chosen scenario.~
-# production plumes sel: Average number of aerially detect production plumes from the chosen scenario that were selected for use in a given Monte Carlo iteration.~
-# prod sources overall: The total number of well site sources emitting at any point during the selected campaign.~
-# avg prod sources sim: The average number of well sites emitting in a given Monte Carlo iteration.~
-# midstream plumes: The total number of plumes attributed to midstream assets in the selected scenario.~
-# midstream sources: The total number of midstream sources identified in the selected scenario.~
-# avg midstream sources sim: Average numer of emitting midstream sources in a given Monte Carlo iteration.~
-Total sim emissions: Total simulated production emissions from the Rutherford et al model. below the transition point.~
-Stratify by covered prod: Stratify the Rutherford et al. simulated emissions by the productivity characteristics of the surveyed region (if Yes). If No, assume the surveyed region is representative of the full simulated basin.~
-Include repeats: If Yes, include repeated aerial asset visits as independent measurements to be simulated separately. If No (default), simulate emissions only once per asset in a given Monte Carlo iteration.~
-Date: The date on which the selected simulation was run. Sometimes includes a numeric counter. Appears in the names of saved files.~
-Remove negative Kairos emissions: If Yes, set to zero any small negative aerially measured emissions introduced from simulated normal error in Kairos measurements. If No (default), leave the negatives in. A Yes value introduces a small upward bias of order 1% or less.~
-Well site visits: Total number of well site measurements/visits (times the aerial survey flew over and collected data over a well site).~
-Avg visits/well site: Average aerial measurements/visits per well site in the selected scenario.~
-SD to SErr factor: Conversion factor from standard deviation to standard error for mean values over the Monte Carlo, accounting for the fact that many assets were measured multiple times in the campaign, but source-level simulations simulate only one emission per site at a given time.~
-SErr of mean total emissions: Standard error of mean percent difference in total estimated emissions from production and midstream in the selected campaign, comparing the total before and after including sub-aerially detectable midstream emissions.~
-SErr of sample mean: Standard error of the sample mean sub-aerial emissions as a percentage of total estimated emissions from production and midstream.~
-Simulation % prod: Production emissions from the Rutherford et al. model below the transition point as a percentage of total estimated production emissions.~
-Aerial % prod: Aerially measured production emissions above the transition point as a percentage of total production emissions.~
-Partial % prod: Estimated aerially detectible missed production emissions in the partial detection range above the transition point as a percentage of total production emissions.~
-Methane fractional loss simulation prod: Methane fractional loss rate based solely on simulated production emissions from the Rutherford et al. model below the transition point.~
-Methane fractional loss simulation prodP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Methane fractional loss simulation prodP97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Methane fractional loss aerial prod: Methane fractional loss based solely on aerially measured production emissions above the transition point.~
-AerialFracLossProdP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-AerialFracLossProdP97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Methane fractional loss partial prod: Methane fractional loss based solely on aerially detectable missed production emissions in the partial detection range above the transition point.~
-Methane fractional loss partial prodP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Methane fractional loss partial prodP97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-FracLossProd: Overall fractional loss for production in the selected scenario, combining all available data sources.~
-FracLossProdP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-FracLossProdP97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Methane fractional loss total: Total methane fractional loss rate, combining all available production and midstream data sources.~
-FracLossP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-FracLossP97.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-FracLossP2.5Full: The 2.5% confidence interval of overall fractional loss, adding the mean.~
-FracLossP97.5Full: The 97.5% confidence interval of overall fractional loss, adding the mean.~
-FracLossMidAerial: Methane fractional loss based solely on aerially measured midstream emissions.~
-FracLossMidAerialP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-FracLossMidAerialP97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-FracLossMidPartial: Methane fractional loss based solely on aerially detectable missed midstream emissions in the partial detection range.~
-FracLossMidPartialP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-FracLossMidPartialP97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-FracLossMidGHGI: Methane fractional loss based solely on estimated midstream emissions below the aerial detection threshold, based on Greenhouse Gas Inventory data and analysis.~
-FracLossMidGHGIP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-FracLossMidGHGIP97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-FracLossMidstream total: Overall midstream methane fractional loss rate estimated by combining all available midstream data sources.~
-FracLossMidstream totalP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-FracLossMidstream totalP97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-% well site visits with plume: The percentage of well site visits (measurements) resulting in an aerially detected emission.~
-% well site visits with selected plume: The percentage of well site visits with an aerially detected emission above the transition point.~
-Fraction sim retained: Fraction of overall emissions from the Rutherford et al. model for the selected scenario that are retained in the final analysis (modeled emissions below the transition point divided by total modeled emission)~
-Well sites covered: Total number of well sites covered (measured) during the campaign underlying the selected scenario.~
-% well sites ever emitting: The percentage of well sites emitting at any point during the campaign underlying the selected scenario.~
-Avg % wells emitting: Average percent of wells emitting during a given Monte Carlo iteration, assuming at most one well per site is emitting.~
-Avg % sites emitting: The average fraction of well sites emitting in a given Monte Carlo iteration.~
-Total aerial: Total aerially measured emissions at production and midstream sites, including only emissions above the transition point. In metric tons per hour.~
-Total aerialP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total aerialP97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total aerial+partial emissions: Total aerially measured emissions at production and midstream sites, including implied emissions in the partial detection range, including only emissions above the transition point. In metric tons per hour.~
-Total aerial+partial emissionsP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total aerial+partial emissionsP97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-¬Total sim emissions: Total simulated emissions below the transition point, including the Rutherford et al. model for production and the GHGI-based midstream emissions estimation.~
-Total sim emissionsP2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total sim emissionsP97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
¬-Total aerial all segments inc below transition: Total aerially measured emissions from production and midstream, including below the transition point. In metric tons per hour.~
-Total aerial all segments inc below transition P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total aerial all segments inc below transition P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total pipeline emissions: Total aerially measured pipeline emissions, in metric tons per hour.~
-Total pipeline emissions P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total pipeline emissions P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total compressor emissions: Total aerially measured compressor emissions, in metric tons per hour.~
-Total compressor emissions P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total compressor emissions P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total processing emissions: Total aerially gas processing plant pipeline emissions, in metric tons per hour.~
-Total processing emissions P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total processing emissions P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total other midstream emissions: Total aerially measured other midstream emissions, in metric tons per hour.~
-Total other midstream emissions P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total other midstream emissions P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Frac aerial: Aerially measured emissions as a fraction of total estimated emissions across the selected campaign. Excludes production emissions below the transition point.~
-Frac aerial+partial: Aerial + partial detection emissions from production and midstream as a fraction of total estimated emissions for the selected campaign.~
¬-¬Frac sim: Simulated emissions as a fraction of total estimated emissions across the selected campaign.~
-Frac midstream: Midstream emissions as a fraction of total estimated emissions from production and midstream.~
-Frac midstream aerial: Aerial midstream emissions as a fraction of total estimated emissions from production and midstream.~
-Total production emissions: Total estimated emissions from well sites surveyed in the selected scenario, accounting for a transition point from simulated to aerially measured emissions.~
-Total/Sim: Total estimated well site emissions as a fraction of total simulated emissions, including those above the transition point.~
-Production/site covered: Average methane production per covered well site in the selected scenario.~
-State GHGI: Natural gas fractional loss rate according to the GHGI in the selected state.~
-NG methane fraction~
-kgCH4 per mcfNG: Kilograms of methane per thousand standard cubic feet of methane, converting from the molar methane fraction assumed in Sherwin, Chen et al. 2021 to the molar methane fraction assumed in this study.~
-Full upper errorbar % total: Upper confidence bound on total methane emissions from production and midstream as a percentage of methane production. 95% confidence interval accounts for the fact that many sites were visited multiple times. Confidence interval presented as a percentage of the mean estimate.~
-Full lower errorbar % total: Lower confidence bound on total methane emissions from production and midstream as a percentage of methane production. 95% confidence interval accounts for the fact that many sites were visited multiple times. Confidence interval presented as a percentage of the mean estimate.~
-Partial prod % total: Production emissions in the partial detection range, implied by detected emissions in the same range, as a fraction of total estimated emissions from both production and midstream.~
-Partial mid % total: midstream emissions in the partial detection range, implied by detected emissions in the same range, as a fraction of total estimated emissions from both production and midstream.~
-Tot sim emissions loss rate: Loss rate from purely simulated emissions, including those above the transition point.~
-Tot sim emissions loss rate P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Tot sim emissions loss rate P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Prod-only state GHGI loss: Production segment (well site) natural gas loss rate according to the state-level GHGI for the selected scenario.~
-Prod-only state GHGI loss low: Low bound of the above (treated as a 2.5% confidence interval).~
-Prod-only state GHGI loss high: Low bound of the above (treated as a 97.5% confidence interval).~
-¬Total aerial prod emissions inc below transition: Total aerially detected production emissions in metric tons per hour, including those below the transition point.~
-Total aerial prod emissions inc below transition P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total aerial prod emissions inc below transition P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total aerial mid emissions inc below transition: Total aerially detected midstream emissions, including below the transition point (if any).~
-Total aerial mid emissions inc below transition P2.5: The 2.5% confidence interval of the above.~
-Total aerial mid emissions inc below transition P97.5: The 97.5% confidence interval of the above.
Definition: IF Key_export_results='Run #'~
	THEN Scenario_unique_ID_s~
ELSE IF Key_export_results='Batch counter'~
	THEN Scenario_batch_count~
ELSE IF Key_export_results='Scenario'~
	THEN Select_scenario~
ELSE IF Key_export_results='Prod simulation (t/h)'~
	THEN Total_emissions_by_8[Emission_component='Engineering simulation',Mean_CI='Mean']~
ELSE IF Key_export_results='Prod simulation P2.5'~
	THEN Total_emissions_by_8[Emission_component='Engineering simulation',Mean_CI='P2.5']~
ELSE IF Key_export_results='Prod simulation P97.5'~
	THEN Total_emissions_by_8[Emission_component='Engineering simulation',Mean_CI='P97.5']~
