Module Midstream_partial_d1
Title: Midstream partial detection
Description: Identify partial detection probabilities for selected midstream emissions.
Author: evands
Date: Sat, Oct 22, 2022 9:19 AM
NodeLocation: 568,176,1
NodeSize: 88,40
DiagState: 2,633,56,937,248,19,10,

Variable Partial_detection_11
Title: Partial detection correction Kairos midstream plumes
Description: The estimated probability of detecting an emission of the selected wind-normalized magnitude.~
Anything smaller than the rated min detect of the instrument is given a correction fraction of 0.2, meaning that if we see one, we assume we missed 5.
Definition: VAR init :=(Kairos_wind_normaliz <= Partial_detect_bin_t)*Selected_probability;~
IF Kairos_wind_normaliz > Max(Partial_detect_bin_t)~
	THEN 1~
ELSE Min(IF init=0~
	THEN Null~
ELSE init, Partial_detect_bin_t)~
{LinearInterp(Partial_detect_bin_t, Selected_probability, Raw_selected_plumes_)}
