Index Aerial_emissions_lar
Title: Aerial emissions larger than transition point index
Description: Aerial emissions larger than the minimum (smallest) aerially measured emission to include.~
Only for use in analyses on a plume-level (site visit-level) rather than on a source-level.
Definition: Mid(Subset((Aerial_average_emis1 >= Min_aerial_emission_)))
NodeLocation: 280,192,1
NodeSize: 80,48
WindState: 2,1049,145,720,350
ValueState: 2,516,522,416,303,0,MIDM

Variable Source_level_aerial2
Title: Source-level aerial emissions larger than transition point
Description: Aerial emissions larger than the transition point in the source-level simulation.
Definition: {FOR jj := Run DO BEGIN~
	INDEX fullEmissionsInAerialRutherfordJointRange := CopyIndex(Emissions_larger_th1[Run=jj]);	~
	INDEX emissionsInAerialRutherfordJointRange := Subset(fullEmissionsInAerialRutherfordJointRange);~
	LinearInterp(emissionsInAerialRutherfordJointRange, Aerial_and_partial_1[Full_distribution_em=emissionsInAerialRutherfordJointRange], Method_crossover_ran, emissionsInAerialRutherfordJointRange)~
END}~
(Sample(Source_level_plume_1) >= Min_aerial_emission_)
