Units: kgh
Description: Total aerially detected emissions included in the final results.
Definition: IF Include_repeats_in_w='Yes'~
	THEN Sum(Aerial_emissions_la1, Aerial_emissions_lar)~
ELSE IF Include_repeats_in_w='No' ~
	THEN Sum(Aerial_emissions_la1, Dummy_plume_consiste)~
ELSE Null
NodeLocation: 280,56,1
NodeSize: 72,40
ValueState: 2,308,314,416,303,,MEAN

Variable Aerial_emissions_la1
Title: Aerial emissions larger than transition point
Units: kgh
Description: Aerially detected emissions larger than the transition point.
Definition: IF Include_repeats_in_w='Yes'~
	THEN Plume_level_aerial_2~
ELSE IF Include_repeats_in_w='No' ~
	THEN Source_level_aerial3~
ELSE Null
NodeLocation: 280,160,1
NodeSize: 72,40
ValueState: 2,508,549,416,303,,MIDM

Variable Aerial_emissions_la5
Title: Aerial emissions larger than transition point sorted
Units: kgh
Description: Sorted emissions that made the cut. Averaged for plume-level.~
Not a perfect 1:1 match with emissions sorted by wind-normalized emission rate, but an approximation.
Definition: IF Include_repeats_in_w='Yes'~
	THEN Plume_level_average_~
ELSE IF Include_repeats_in_w='No' ~
	THEN Source_level_aerial4~
ELSE Null
NodeLocation: 280,264,1
NodeSize: 72,40
ValueState: 2,678,423,416,303,,SAMP

Variable Source_level_aerial3
Title: Source-level aerial emissions larger than transition point
Units: kgh
Description: Aerially detected emissions larger than the transition point, on a well site-level basis (at most one emission per site).~
Sets zeros to null.
Definition: VAR init := Source_level_aerial2*Source_level_plume_1;~
IF init=0~
	THEN Null~
ELSE init
NodeLocation: 104,160,1
NodeSize: 72,40
WindState: 2,17,557,720,350
ValueState: 2,157,224,451,498,,SAMP

Variable Source_level_aerial4
Title: Source-level aerial emissions larger than TP sorted ascend
Units: kgh
Description: Sorts selected emissions for each iteration.
Definition: Sort(Source_level_aerial3, Dummy_plume_consiste)
NodeLocation: 104,264,1
NodeSize: 72,40
WindState: 2,0,72,720,350
ValueState: 2,372,493,797,303,0,SAMP

Variable Plume_level_aerial_2
Title: Plume-level aerial emissions larger than transition point
Units: kgh
Description: Aerially detected emissions larger than the transition point, on a well site visit-level basis (treating multiple visits to the same site as independent measurements).
Definition: Aerial_prod_emissio2[Dummy_plume_consiste=Aerial_emissions_lar];
NodeLocation: 456,160,1
NodeSize: 72,40
ValueState: 2,508,549,416,303,,MIDM

Variable Plume_level_average_
Title: Plume-level average aerial emissions larger than TP sorted
Units: kgh
Description: Sorted average emissions that made the cut.~
Not a perfect 1:1 match with emissions sorted by wind-normalized emission rate, but an approximation.
Definition: Sort(Mean(Plume_level_aerial_2, Run), Aerial_emissions_lar)
NodeLocation: 456,264,1
NodeSize: 72,40

